So this past week sucked on quite a few levels but was good on one or two.  My grandmother passed away on friday, before i had a chance to see her one last time, got to spend easter with family that i havent seen in a long time.  Monday was the wake, Tuesday was the funeral at which i was a pall bearer (not fun).  but i got to meet this really cool and cute girl Casey, and I got to see my cousin meagan ( my lil rebel princess) and her brothers matt and paul, and Paul's girlfriend brittany. 

Dan

I know, it's been forever since I last posted, but here's what's up:

First of all, the Kenny Concert was awesome.  We ended up in the upper section, with a birds eye view of the stage, but we still had a great time.  

Since then, I got a job at Burger King on the closing shift which is pretty cool, considering I can get a discount on my food.  

I started my third year at FSC, so good so far, thinking about switching my major from psychology to philosophy or communications media.

The icing on the cake, though, was Locobazooka.  Why, you ask?  Not just because the Dropkick Murphy's co-headlined with Disturbed, but because I got on stage with the Dropkick Murphy's.

Til next time, (I promise, it won't be another 3 months!)

Alright so Saturday night I went to my first real Dogfight show, and it F'n rocked!!!!  By the way, Dogfight is a kik-ass band from Boston that all of you out there should chek out.  So anyways, the show was in tewksbury and there were 2 other bands there, Reaxis and Exhale.  Reaxis was OK but Exhale rather sucked.  By the time Dogfight came on it was 11 o'clock, I was right up front, not even 2 feet from the guys.  Plus I got to meet the lead singer Mike and the drummer Danny!! I'm still a little sore from all the head rocking.  The website is http://www.dogfightband.com, check it out!

Dan
